
[1]transcursion

   TRANSCUR'SION, n. [supra.] A rambling or ramble; a passage beyond
   certain limits; extraordinary deviation; as the transcursion of a
   comet.

   I am to make often transcursions into the neighboring
   forests as I pass along.

       [Note: Excursion has in a great measure superseded this word.]
